ln the expression ‘iuris praecepta,' ius seems hardly to bear any ol these meanings‚ for the precept ‘honeste vivere’ is rather an ethical principle than a rule of positive law; at least men often practise what cannot be termed an honest calling without bringing themselves within reach of the law.
